RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 4 4F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Special Weight Purse 8500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND OLDER. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LILY PAD LAKE Led along the rail from the outset in a line of three, opened up on two outside challengers in the run around the bend commencing at the quarter pole, extended lead from eighth pole to wire in a convincing victory. IGO Broke best, vied between rivals up backstretch, attempted to stick with eventual winner to the top of the home stretch, pursued throughout lane, no match. MISS MY MAMMA Pressed three wide in backstretch run, called upon at the three-sixteenths while travelling the widest of the three early speeds, urged yet finished up evenly in the four path. DUKE CITY KITTY Taken ahold of between in opening stages, pressed along by rider at the quarter pole yet idled against commands, found best stride in final two hundred yards, showed strong late headway between while passing two tiring foes. L'ARACHIDE Tracked in the second flight of runners in the three path, attempted to threaten at the quarter pole, chased down the stretch, tired. LITTLEQUEENOFMEAN Broke in order but shied soon after the start as the field progressed past the backstretch chute, recovered to maintain contact with field while still in rear, advanced at three-eighths pole in the form of a mild bid that flattened out gradually through the homestretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Littlequeenofmean
ENTRY.COMMENT: Shied towards gap, advanced 3/8ths, mild bid, flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Duke City Kitty
ENTRY.COMMENT: Taken ahold of, pressed on 1/4, idled, headway passed tiring

ENTRY.NAME: L'Arachide
ENTRY.COMMENT: Tracked 2nd flight 3p, move ins 1/4, chased lane, tired

ENTRY.NAME: Lily Pad Lake
ENTRY.COMMENT: Led rail, opened up 1/4 to 1/8, drew off

ENTRY.NAME: Igo
ENTRY.COMMENT: Broke best, vied between, pursued lane, no match for winner

ENTRY.NAME: Miss My Mamma
ENTRY.COMMENT: Pressed 3w backside, ask 3/16ths widest challenger, evenly

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 7600. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MAY 23, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOST THE MINISTER Was unable to save ground in run to the first turn and ended up in the six path, tracked widest of all rivals as backstretch loomed, commenced a four wide bid while travelling in hand at the quarter pole, fought willingly deepest of a three horse stretch run, lifted in the final hundred yards, powered through wire. RED HOT CAT Could not tuck in, forced five wide into the first turn, moved up to challenge for the lead two wide in the four path at the seven-sixteenths pole, sustained bid three wide in run around turn, battled between, made a brief lead at the sixteenth pole that was short live as he was outfinished by the eventual winner. OMACHE KID Checked slightly between in run to first turn, recovered quickly to sit just in behind dueling leaders, moved up three wide at the seven-sixteenths pole, commenced three wide while still in the second flight at the quarter pole, fully found top gear at the sixteenth pole, picked up well for show. EMPEROR'S CHOICE Worked hard to get over, eventually set up two wide while dueling for the lead, fully assumed lead at the three-eighths pole, soon joined at the five-sixteenths pole by rival outside while still fending off inside rival, finally cleared to lead and the rail at the quarter pole, opened up a shortly lived lead at the eighth pole, run down by closing foes at the sixteenth pole, had nothing left late. SHELBY R. Led from the outset, joined by a rival outside at the seven-sixteenths pole, conceded lead while still holding the rail at the three-eighths pole, switched to the two path at the three-sixteenths pole for an attempted rebid, flattened out down the stretch. ROLL OUT Saved ground in a pocket in first turn run, travelled in same spot before being sent at the quarter pole, was all dressed up with nowhere to go while stuck behind rival in front and outside from one hundred-fifty yards out to the wire. W. WHITEHOUSE Taken ahold of early, always travelled on the rail, never a factor. TROPHY CHEST Was a touch slow from the blocks, moved two wide in rear on the first turn, maintained position, shifted well out to the five path on the second turn, never really involved.

ENTRY.NAME: W. Whitehouse
ENTRY.COMMENT: Taken ahold of, rail throughout, never a factor

ENTRY.NAME: Trophy Chest
ENTRY.COMMENT: Touch slow break, 2w first, 5p second, never involved

ENTRY.NAME: Shelby R.
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: Led, conceded 3/8, switch 2p 3/16, flattened out

ENTRY.NAME: Roll Out
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: Save ground in pocket, sent 1/4, nowhere to go 150 yards

ENTRY.COMMENT: Check btwn 1st, moved up 3w 7/16, 3w bid 1/4, gained 1/16

ENTRY.NAME: Emperor's Choice
ENTRY.COMMENT: Duel outs, assumed 3/8, joined 5/16, rail 1/4, run down 1/16

ENTRY.NAME: Red Hot Cat
ENTRY.COMMENT: 5w first, challenged lead 2w 4p, battle between, outfinished

ENTRY.NAME: Lost the Minister
ENTRY.OWNER: Crotts James E and Jaime Jr Jacobo
ENTRY.COMMENT: 6w 1st, tracked, 4w travelling well, willingly 3 deep, lifted

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 6 4F Dirt CR: 80. Allowance Purse 9000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE SEPTEMBER 23, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIME TO ZOOM Quickly assumed between rivals shortly after the break, opened up a clear advantage at the quarter pole, shook home on the wrong lead while striding home convincingly. KING LEBRON Moved up along the rail to battle for the early lead, was outsprinted by TIME TO ZOOM as field wielded into the far turn, chased that rival all the way to the wire. TAKE CHARGE DEPUTY Taken back inside while watching duel unfold, commenced rail rally at the quarter pole, flew home inside for minor awards. SAN GIORGIO Travelled in the five path in backside run, circled three wide into the turn, presented a mild belated gain. TIZ A SPEED BOMB Three wide dueling for early lead, outrun in move to the turn, taken to the rail at the three-sixteenths pole, gave way stretch. CURRENTLY KRAZY Tracked off the lead, moved three wide into the turn, moved further out to pass tiring, eventually well out in center of track for stretch, ran moderately down lane. EPIC ADVENTURE Was away extremely sharply but was then surely outrun by inside trio who went on to duel, dropped back between horses at the quarter pole, faded.

ENTRY.NAME: King Lebron
ENTRY.OWNER: Crotts James E and Valenzuela Angel
ENTRY.COMMENT: Moved up rail, outsprinted by winner, always chasing

ENTRY.NAME: Time to Zoom
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: Quickly assumed between, opened up 1/4, wrong lead, convincingly

ENTRY.NAME: Tiz a Speed Bomb
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w, outrun on turn, moved rail 3/16ths, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Take Charge Deputy
ENTRY.COMMENT: Taken back ins, commenced 1/4, rail rally, flew home

ENTRY.NAME: Currently Krazy
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w into turn, 4w into lane well out in center, moderate late

ENTRY.NAME: Epic Adventure
ENTRY.COMMENT: Sharply away, outrun by inside trio, dropped back 1/4 to wire

ENTRY.NAME: San Giorgio
ENTRY.COMMENT: 5w backside, 3w into turn, mild belated gain

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 76. Allowance Purse 9000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HUGHIE'S HOLIDAY Pinched slightly at the start, taken back and moved to the rail for first turn run, took advantage of preceding foe on rail getting out in run, snuck through in an aggressive move to challenge for the lead at the seven-sixteenths pole, dueled inside of rival for majority of race, just kept going. KIND BUT SHE LIES Settled two wide in first turn run, left rail open for inside rival to come engage at the seven-sixteenths pole, dueled outside until the eighth pole, fought willingly through stretch, second best. HAYNESPUN Moved four wide into the first turn, settled to track leaders, asked at the quarter pole in the three path, moved to the rail at the three-sixteenths pole for an inside bid that was thwarted by the top two finishers. PRINCESS SUGEITH Five wide first turn, never in touch with top three finishers. AWESOME GALAXY Travelled three wide into the first turn, eventually taken back, never involved from that point and passed one tiring foe. ARCTIC FIRE Set up on rail for run to first turn but became uncomfortable between the pine and rival outside, set up second flight, never menaced.

ENTRY.NAME: Arctic Fire
ENTRY.COMMENT: Uncomfy 1st, 2nd flight, never menaced

ENTRY.NAME: Kind But She Lies
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2w, left rail open, duel outs, willingly, second best

ENTRY.NAME: Awesome Galaxy
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w first turn, taken back, never involved, passed one tiring

ENTRY.NAME: Haynespun
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4w tracking, asked 1/4, 3w bid, move rail 3/16, bid thwarted

ENTRY.NAME: Hughie's Holiday
ENTRY.COMMENT: Pinch brk, move rail, snuck thru 7/16ths, duel ins, kept going

ENTRY.NAME: Princess Sugeith
ENTRY.COMMENT: 5w, always out of touch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 8100. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE AUGUST 26, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FIRST COUNT Broke best, cleared to rail and lead, joined by outer rival briefly that was brushed off at the three-eighths pole, maintained lead, two path stretch, held off one more trying foe, drew off. STONUS MAXIMUS Three wide in contention first turn, let inner rivals progress which allowed horse to stalk up backstretch in the three path, moved to the two path for turn, dove to rail at the eighth pole to challenge leader, was held off by that foe, just held pass while tiring to wire. FOCUS FIRST Four path into the first turn, settled off the pace, moved up in three path at the three-sixteenths pole, sustained rally throughout, just missed place. WISHFUL WON Stalked behind leaders first, failed to menace. AUTISM SAVANT Well wide and lagging first, never in contention, passed tiring. TRIPDOWNMEMORYLANE Missed break, quickly moved up to track inside second turn, asked at the five-sixteenths pole while moving along the rail, came home evenly. CANT DO THE DANSE Let FIRST COUNT clear off, switched between in run to first turn to duel two wide, failed to keep pace with leader, asked at three-eighths pole to find more, showed no response, plummeted through the field.

ENTRY.NAME: Cant Do the Danse
ENTRY.OWNER: Pallanes, Alan J. and Arnold, Pete
ENTRY.COMMENT: Hustled to challenge 2w, asked 3/8, no response, plummeted

ENTRY.NAME: First Count
ENTRY.COMMENT: Rail, led, brushed off challenge, 2p str, drew off

ENTRY.NAME: Tripdownmemorylane
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: Missed break, tracked ins 2nd turn, ask 5/16 rail, evenly

ENTRY.NAME: Autism Savant
ENTRY.COMMENT: Well wide and lagging first, never in contention, passed tiring

ENTRY.NAME: Wishful Won
ENTRY.COMMENT: Stalked behind leaders first, failed to menace

ENTRY.NAME: Stonus Maximus
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w first, move 2p lane, shift rail 1/8th, held place

ENTRY.NAME: Focus First
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4p turn, off pace 3p at 3/16, sustained rally, just missed place
